		<div id="body_text">
			
			<p>The GenderMag Method consists of a gender-specialized cognitive walkthrough and a set of four GenderMag personas.</p>
            
			<h3>GenderMag Resources</h3>
            
            <ul>
                <li><i>Flyer</i>: A <a href="./downloadables/genderMag-flyer.pdf">one-page flyer about GenderMag</a>.</li>
		<li><i>Talks:</i>
		  <ul>
		    <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6HYvp5GrPjU&list=PLeMUfrwZ5THp_sYBgXZCl1pC5rQL_4Y2j&t=10s&index=10">20-minute talk on GenderMag (a field study) at CHI'16</a></li>
                    <li>The <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z6NUbguJTak&t=177s&list=PLeMUfrwZ5THp_sYBgXZCl1pC5rQL_4Y2j&index=11">Burnett Distinguished Professor Lecture on GenderMag</a> (about 60 minutes), presented May 2016. (The actual talk starts about 3 minutes in.) Other talks and papers about GenderMag can be found <a href="http://web.engr.oregonstate.edu/~burnett/reprints.html">here</a>.</li>
		    </ul></li>
                <li><i>Kit</i>: The <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1NXjpj7NSGuVScPdR9EJgzv-eeKM9-NOY4gP9B0Dpf4U/viewform?edit_requested=true">kit</a> for using the method (beta version). The latest version is July 2017.  (Or, <a HREF="mailto:burnett@eecs.oregonstate.edu?subject=obtain GenderMag">request that a copy be sent to you via email</a> (2 MB).)</li>
                <ul>
                    <li><i>Other downloadables</i>: Editable/customizable <a href="./downloadables/">personas and forms</a> in editable formats to use with the kit.</li>
                </ul>
                <li><i>Foundations</i>: The <a href="http://eusesconsortium.org/gender/GenderMagPersona-FoundationDocuments/Foundations.html">personas foundations document</a>.  The latest version is Nov. 12, 2015.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Related Resources</h3>
            
            <ul>
                <li><a href="http://www.ncwit.org">National Center for Women in Technology (NCWIT)</a>: a great collection of resources on many aspects of gender and technology.</li>
                <li><a href="http://eusesconsortium.org/gender/genderRelated.php">Gender HCI Publications Resource</a> for those interested in Gender HCI research.</li>
                <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gender_HCI">Wikipedia Entry</a> on Gender HCI.</li>
            </ul>
			
